    <note>Li Tao [1094] The founder of this branch of the Longxi jun Li(2) Tang imperial family was Caogong wang, Ming [13882] (the #14 and youngest son of Tang Taizong), whose youngest son, Si [13883], was expunged from the imperial registers (ji) by empress Wu, made a commoner and moved to Meizhou, Danleng xian. Si's sixth generation descendant. Yu [13884], was again included in the registers for the first time. Yu was a county magistrate and grandfather of Dao's great grandfather Kui(2) [13885]. Jiangxi TZ, 10.20b; Zhou Bida, WJ, 66.7b-23b; Shengzheng, 54.14a; Wang Deyu, Li Dao fuzi nianpu, pp. 3, 7, 11, 61, 104. CBD, 2, 925-7.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1174:  Apt. Jiangnan Xi yunfu1175:  In office as Jiangnan Xi yunfu</note>
